TITLE: Creating Custom Configuration with Custom Transforms - JavaScript ES Module
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript ES Module exports a Style Dictionary configuration object. It allows advanced setup such as registering custom transforms (e.g., 'myTransform'), formats (e.g., 'myFormat'), filters, and more, beyond what is possible in plain JSON. Requires the Style Dictionary package and (optionally) knowledge of its registration APIs. Key parameters define transforms, formats, source files, and platforms. Inputs include token definitions; outputs are generated style files customized via the defined logic. Limitations: This format is not supported by CLI tools expecting only JSON.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/reference/config.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export default {
  source: [`tokens/**/*.json`],
  // If you don't want to call the registerTransform method a bunch of times
  // you can override the whole transform object directly. This works because
  // the .extend method copies everything in the config
  // to itself, allowing you to override things. It's also doing a deep merge
  // to protect from accidentally overriding nested attributes.
  transform: {
    // Now we can use the transform 'myTransform' below
    myTransform: {
      type: transformTypes.name,
      transform: (token) => token.path.join('_').toUpperCase(),
    },
  },
  // Same with formats, you can now write them directly to this config
  // object. The name of the format is the key.
  format: {
    myFormat: ({ dictionary, platform }) => {
      return dictionary.allTokens.map((token) => `${token.name}: ${token.value};`).join('\n');
    },
  },
  platforms: {
    // ...
  },
};
```

