TITLE: Registering Custom Format with fileHeader in Style Dictionary (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to create a custom file format in Style Dictionary using the fileHeader helper for prepending standardized comments. The snippet demonstrates importing commentStyles, configuring header style, and concatenating a header comment to token output. Requires the 'style-dictionary' library and optionally custom formatting options via the fileHeader function. Expects a dictionary (with allTokens) and file object, outputs formatted property lines with a generated comment header prepended.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/reference/Utils/format-helpers.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { commentStyles } from 'style-dictionary/enums';

StyleDictionary.registerFormat({
  name: 'myCustomFormat',
  format: async ({ dictionary, file }) => {
    const header = await fileHeader({ file, commentStyle: commentStyles.short });
    return (
      header + dictionary.allTokens.map((token) => `${token.name} = ${token.value};`).join('\n')
    );
  },
});
```

