TITLE: Manually Deferring Transitive Transformation (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet shows a custom transitive value transform that checks if a specific token property (`token.darken`) relies on a reference using `usesReferences`. If the `darkenModifier` is a reference, the transform returns `undefined` to defer the transformation until the reference is resolved in a later cycle. Otherwise, it applies the `darken` function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/reference/Hooks/Transforms/index.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```js title="build-tokens.js"
import { StyleDictionary } from 'style-dictionary';
import { usesReferences } from 'style-dictionary/utils';

StyleDictionary.registerTransform({
  name: '',
  type: transformTypes.value,
  transitive: true,
  transform: (token) => {
    const darkenModifier = token.darken;
    if (usesReferences(darkenModifier)) {
      // defer this transform, because our darken value is a reference
      return undefined;
    }
    return darken(token.value, darkenModifier);
  },
});
```
