TITLE: Registering a Custom Action with Style Dictionary in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates registering a custom action globally using the `StyleDictionary.registerAction` class method. The example defines an action to copy assets, providing asynchronous `do` and `undo` functions that utilize `fs.promises`. Registered actions can be used within platform configurations to extend build or clean processes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/reference/api.mdx#_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
StyleDictionary.registerAction({
  name: actions.copyAssets,
  do: async function (dictionary, config) {
    console.log('Copying assets directory');
    await fs.promises.copy('assets', config.buildPath + 'assets');
  },
  undo: async function (dictionary, config) {
    console.log('Cleaning assets directory');
    await fs.promises.remove(config.buildPath + 'assets');
  },
});
```

