TITLE: Initializing Style Dictionary with an In-Memory Filesystem (memfs) in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the `volume` option when creating a Style Dictionary instance to work with an in-memory filesystem provided by `memfs`. This allows isolating file operations. The example defines tokens and a CSS platform configuration directly in the object, builds the platform, and then reads the generated file from the virtual volume. Requires `memfs` or a prebundled version.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/reference/api.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: js
