TITLE: Registering Custom Format Inferring TypeScript Types with getTypeScriptType (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates generating TypeScript-compatible constants with type annotations by leveraging the getTypeScriptType helper. The snippet maps over all tokens and constructs export statements with inferred type names, optionally appending prop comments. Requires getTypeScriptType and a Style Dictionary-formatted token dictionary. Outputs export statements for each token in a TypeScript-friendly format.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/reference/Utils/format-helpers.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
StyleDictionary.registerFormat({
  name: 'myCustomFormat',
  format: function ({ dictionary, options }) {
    return dictionary.allTokens
      .map(function (prop) {
        var to_ret_prop = 'export const ' + prop.name + ' : ' + getTypeScriptType(prop.value) + ';';
        if (prop.comment) to_ret_prop = to_ret_prop.concat(' // ' + prop.comment);
        return to_ret_prop;
      })
      .join('\n');
  },
});
```

