TITLE: Custom Format Registration and Usage in Style Dictionary (JavaScript, Formats)
DESCRIPTION: This example registers and applies a custom format handler for Style Dictionary using both the global registry and the new 'hooks.formats' property in v4. It shows the rename from 'formatter' to 'format' and related typing imports. Dependencies: Style Dictionary v4+, correct TypeScript type imports if typing is used. Parameters: dictionary object; output: stringified JSON. Also demonstrates linking the format to platforms/files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/version-4/migration.md#_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import StyleDictionary from 'style-dictionary';
import type { Formatter, FormatterArguments } from 'style-dictionary/types';
import type { FormatFn, FormatFnArguments } from 'style-dictionary/types';

// register it with register method
StyleDictionary.registerFormat({
  name: 'custom/json',
  formatter: ({ dictionary }) => JSON.stringify(dictionary, null, 2),
  format: ({ dictionary }) => JSON.stringify(dictionary, null, 2),
})

export default {
  // OR define it inline
  format: {
    'custom/json': ({ dictionary }) => JSON.stringify(dictionary, null, 2),
  },
  hooks: {
    formats: {
      'custom/json': ({ dictionary }) => JSON.stringify(dictionary, null, 2),
    },
  },
  platforms: {
    json: {
      files: [{
        destination: 'output.json',
        format: 'custom/json'
      }],
    },
  },
};
```

