TITLE: Updating Parser Hook Registration (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows the breaking change in how parsers are registered and applied in Style Dictionary v4 configuration. Parsers are now defined within a `hooks.parsers` object (instead of a top-level `parsers` array), using a unique key (e.g., 'json5-parser'). The handler function property name is changed from `parse` to `parser`. Crucially, registered parsers must now be explicitly applied by referencing their key in a top-level `parsers` array within the configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/version-4/migration.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```js title="config.js" del={3-10} ins={9-24} /parse(r): (/
export default {
  // register it inline or by SD.registerPreprocessor
  parsers: [
    {
      pattern: /\.json5$/,
      parse: ({ contents, filePath }) => {
        return JSON5.parse(contents);
      },
    },
  ],
  hooks: {
    parsers: {
      'json5-parser': {
        pattern: /\.json5$/,
        parser: ({ contents, filePath }) => {
          return JSON5.parse(contents);
        },
      },
    },
  },
  // apply it globally by name reference
  parsers: ['json5-parser'],
};
```
```

