TITLE: Updating Custom Formatters Signature in Style Dictionary (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates the required update to the custom formatter function signature in Style Dictionary. The previous signature accepting `dictionary, platform, file` as separate arguments is deprecated. The new signature accepts a single object `{ dictionary, file, options }` as its argument. It also shows that options like `outputReferences` are now accessed via the `options` key (destructured from the single argument object) instead of `file.options`, and highlights that the `fileHeader` utility function is now asynchronous and must be awaited.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/version-4/migration.md#_snippet_39

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
```js title="build-tokens.js" del={8,10} ins={9,11}
import StyleDictionary from 'style-dictionary';

// yes, this is another breaking change, more on that later
import { fileHeader } from 'style-dictionary/utils';

StyleDictionary.registerFormat({
  name: 'custom/css',
  formatter: async function (dictionary, platform, file) {
  format: async function ({ dictionary, file, options }) {
    const { outputReferences } = file.options;
    const { outputReferences } = options;
    return (
      fileHeader({ file }) +
      // this helper is now async! because the user-passed file.fileHeader might be an async function
      (await fileHeader({ file })) +
      ':root {\n' +
      formattedVariables({ format: 'css', dictionary, outputReferences }) +
      '\n}\n'
    );
  },
});
```
```

