TITLE: Registering a Custom Format with sortByName using Style Dictionary (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the sortByName function within a custom Style Dictionary format for token sorting. This code registers a format that sorts dictionary.allTokens by their names using the sortByName comparator, maps each token to a name-value string, and joins them by newline. Dependencies: StyleDictionary module and sortByName utility. Inputs: dictionary.allTokens array. Outputs: newline-separated list of token assignments sorted by name. Suitable for targets expecting ordered declarations, aiding readability and consistency.
