TITLE: Using Style-Dictionary Enum-Like Objects in Configuration (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates importing and applying enum-like objects (formats, log levels, transform groups and transforms) from 'style-dictionary/enums' in an instantiation of a StyleDictionary configuration. It shows how enums enhance type safety and avoid hardcoded strings for key configuration options. Requires the 'style-dictionary' package and access to the 'style-dictionary/enums' module. Inputs include sources, platforms, and logging options; outputs are a configured StyleDictionary instance. Limitations: assumes the file structure and enums are accessible as described.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/reference/enums.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import StyleDictionary from 'style-dictionary';\nimport {\n  formats,\n  logBrokenReferenceLevels,\n  logWarningLevels,\n  logVerbosityLevels,\n  transformGroups,\n  transforms,\n} from 'style-dictionary/enums';\n\nconst sd = new StyleDictionary({\n  source: ['tokens/*.json'],\n  platforms: {\n    scss: {\n      transformGroup: transformGroups.scss,\n      transforms: [transforms.nameKebab],\n      buildPath: 'build/',\n      files: [\n        {\n          destination: 'variables.scss',\n          format: formats.scssVariables,\n        },\n      ],\n    },\n  },\n  log: {\n    warnings: logWarningLevels.warn,\n    verbosity: logVerbosityLevels.verbose,\n    errors: {\n      brokenReferences: logBrokenReferenceLevels.throw,\n    },\n  },\n});
```

