TITLE: Installing Project Dependencies using npm (Shell)
DESCRIPTION: This shell command uses the Node Package Manager (npm) to install all the dependencies listed in the project's `package.json` file. This is a prerequisite step before building or running the Style Dictionary project.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/examples/advanced/npm-module/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
npm install
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Installing Project Dependencies with npm (Bash)
DESCRIPTION: This command uses the Node Package Manager (npm) to download and install all the dependencies listed in the project's `package.json` file. This is the first step required after obtaining the project code to set up the development environment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/examples/complete/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
$ npm install
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Installing Dependencies using npm ci (Shell)
DESCRIPTION: Installs project dependencies cleanly based on the `package-lock.json` file, ensuring a consistent dependency tree across different environments. This command requires npm version 5.7.0 or higher and is the preferred method for installing dependencies after cloning the repository.
SOURCE: https://github.com/amzn/style-dictionary/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
npm ci
```
